The paper discusses a machine learning model (Hierarchical Mixture of Experts) and proposes a Bayesian treatment of the model using variational inference. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with regression and classification tasks, which are common in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of the model for robot arm kinematics also suggests that the paper may belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The model optimization and structure selection aspects of the paper may also make it relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of the model for robotics applications may suggest that the paper belongs to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
